It was in no hurry to move and allowed a close approach. The image was taken in harsh overhead light at midday; I used fill-flash to enhance facial details .........................sometimes I almost sound like I know what I'm doing!  ;-)   Re-worked and framed by a friend.

canavalia-flower;leaf;thumbnail1.creator: David  Eickhoff
canavalia-flower;leaf;thumbnail1.comments: ʻĀwikiwiki or Puakauhi Fabaceae Endemic to the Hawaiian Islands Oʻahu (Cultivated)  This photo was taken on Dec. 21, 2005  Flowers used for lei making. Early Hawaiians made roughly constructed fish nets and traps from stems and scoop nets probably made from ʻāwikiwiki vines for small rock paoʻo (blennies) and ʻopae (freshwater shrimps).  Another ʻāwikiwiki (Canavalia galeata) was specifically mentioned for medicinal purposes. An infusion of leaves, shoots and bark mixed with other plants as a bath for itch, ringworm and skin disorders.  nativeplants.hawaii.edu

tamarindusindica-drawing;thumbnail4.comments: German: Tamarindenbaum. A blühender Zweig, natürl. Grösse; 1 Blüthe ohne Kelchblätter, vergrössert; 2 Staubgefässplatte mit den fruchtbaren und verkümmerten Staubgefässen und den verkümmerten Kronenblättern, desgl.; 3 Staubgefäss, desgl.; 4 Pollen, desgl.; 5 Stempel, desgl.; 6 reife Frucht, natürl. Grösse; 7 dieselbe von der Rinde befreit, mit blosgelegten Gefässbündeln, desgl.; 8 dieselbe im Längsschnitt, um die Samenfächer zu zeigen, desgl.; 9 Same, desgl.; 10, 11 derselbe im Längs- und Querschnitt, desgl.  Latin: Tamarindus indica.  Russian: Тамаринд индийский. A — цветущая ветвь; 1 — цветок без чашелистиков; 2 — тычинки, неразвитые тычинки и неразвитые лепестки; 3 — тычинка; 4 — пыльца; 5 — пестик; 6 — спелый плод (боб); 7 — то же без экзокарпия, с волокнами; 8 — то же в продольном разрезе, с семенами; 9 — семя; 10, 11 — то же в поперечном и продольном разрезе.

cercopithecusmitis-general;thumbnail1.creator: Flickr
cercopithecusmitis-general;thumbnail1.comments: 5 October 2009 - Jozani Forest (Jozani-Chwaka Bay National Park), Zanzibar, Tanzania.  Sykes' Monkey or White-throated Monkey / Witkeelmeerkat (Cercopithecus albogularis), subspecies: Zanzibar Sykes' Monkey / Zanzibar Witkeelmeerkat (Cercopithecus albogularis albogularis).  Subspecies Zanzibar Sykes' Monkey is also known as Cercopithecus mitis albogularis.  There is some dispute about the classification: is this Blue Monkey from Zanzibar a species (if so, what species, C. mitis or C. albogularis?) or a subspecies (C. m. albogularis or C. a. albogularis?). If anybody has an conclusive answer, please leave a comment.  For those who like the biological details: Click a link and you'll go to the Flickr photo page for that rank in the biological classification. You can also add a sponge or Loofah that is all natural and they will get the same results. The brighter the sponge the more bees you will attract. Do not add sponges that have chemicals like soap added for cleaning.   Shot in my backyard in San Angelo Texas.

oryzasativa-drawing.creator: Franz Eugen Köhler, Köhler's Medizinal-Pflanzen
oryzasativa-drawing.comments: German: Reis. A blühendes Exemplar der Pflanze (var. melanoceras Alef.), unterer Teil. B Blütenrispe. C Fruchtrispe der var. italica Körnicke. D Fruchtzweig der var. Sundanensis Körnicke. 1 ein Ährchen von A; 2 dasselbe im Längsschnitt; 3 Staubblätter; 4 Ährchen stärker vergrössert nach Entfernung der unteren (grösseren) Spelze und eines Perigonblattes; 5 Endosperm mit Keimling von C; 6 Scheinfrucht von C im Längsschnitt; 7 Frucht von D; 8 dieselbe im Querschnitt. A, B, C, D etwas verkleinert; 1 bis 7 vergrössert.  Latin: Oryza sativa.  Russian: Рис посевной. A — цветущий экземпляр растения (var. melanoceras Alef.), нижняя часть; B — метелка; C — часть растения с плодами (зерновками), относящегося к var. italica Körnicke. D — часть растения с плодами, относящегос к var. Sundanensis Körnicke. 1 — колосок растения A; 2 — то же в продольном разрезе; 3 — тычинка; 4 — колосок, увелич., после удаления нижней (большей) цветковой чешуи; 5 — эндосперм и зародыш растения C; 6 — зерновка растения C в продольном разрезе; 7 — зерновка растения D; 8 — то же в поперечном разрезе.

passergriseus-pres.creator: Totodu74
passergriseus-pres.comments:
English: 1=A mounted specimen of a sparrow at the Muséum d'histoire naturelle de Genève, said to be "Passer griseus". This probably is a Northern Grey-headed Sparrow—Passer griseus in the strict sense—given the white throat patch and the description of the range of the species ("Ouest et centre de l'Afrique") at the museum, though the Swahili Sparrow and Southern Grey-headed Sparrow would be difficult to distinguish; if it is a Northern Grey-headed Sparrow, it probably is the nominate subspecies griseus.  French: 1=Spécimen empaillé monté de Moineau gris (Passer griseus) au Muséum d'histoire naturelle de Genève, probablement la sous-espèce type. :Écriteau lié : 
Moineau gris
Passer griseus (Vieillot)
Ouest et centre de l'Afrique.

mopsmidas-thumbnail1.creator: inaturalist
mopsmidas-thumbnail1.comments: Mops midas, Midas free-tailed bat, is a large bodied bat with an average mass around 45g. It is grey above with white flecks and paler below (dirty white). Like all Molossids, M. midas has a tail that is not enclosed by a membrane. It is an open-air forager and due to robust skull morphological features and diet studies, it is suggested that it feeds predominantly on beetles (Coleopterans).

colaacuminata-drawing;seed;leaf;thumbnai.creator: Franz Eugen Köhler, Köhler's Medizinal-Pflanzen
colaacuminata-drawing;seed;leaf;thumbnai.comments: German: Kolanuss. A Blattzweig 2/3 natürlicher Grösse. 1 Fruchtlängsschnitt 2/3; 2 roter Samen ohne Schale 1/1; 3 weisser Samen ohne Schale 1/1; 4 Querschnitt 1/1; 5 Längsschnitt desselben in der Richtung a b; em Embryo 1/1; 6 derselbe von einem weissen Samen; 7 Längsschnitt in der Richtung c d, die Insertion der Keimblätter am Embryo zeigend.  Latin: Cola acuminata.  Russian: Кола заострённая (побег, плоды). A — ветвь с листьями; 1 — плод в продольном разрезе; 2 — красное семя без семенной кожуры; 3 — белое семя без семенной кожуры; 4 — поперечный разрез семени; 5 — продольный разрез красного семени по a—b; 6 — то же для белого семени; 7 — продольный разрез по c—d.

daucuscarota-flower.creator: José María Escolano
daucuscarota-flower.comments: Zaragoza: Aragón (España)   Familia: APIACEAE Distribución:    Asia, N de África y por todo Europa; en toda la Península Ibérica y todo Aragón, excepto los ambientes con clima más extremo. Puede formar grandes poblaciones en prados, pastos secos, eriales y cunetas. Las zanahorias de cultivo corresponden a la subsp. sativus (Hoffm.) Schübl. & C. Martens, caracterizada por la raiz napiforme y carnosa seleccionada para el consumo.  Hábitat:    Prados de siega, herbazales subnitrófilos, márgenes de cultivo, eriales y otros ambientes abiertos ya sean algo húmedos o secos. Preferencia edáfica:   Indiferente.    Aparece en todo tipo de sustratos. Rango altitudinal: 200- 1400 ( 1600 ) m Floración:    Marzo - Septiembre ( Octubre ) Fructificación:    Mayo - Octubre ( Noviembre ) Forma Biológica:   Hemicriptófito bienal  Extractado del Atlas de la Flora de Aragón (Herbario de Jaca)

nicotianarustica-drawing.creator: Franz Eugen Köhler, Köhler's Medizinal-Pflanzen
nicotianarustica-drawing.comments: German: Bauern-Tabak. A blühende Pflanze in natürl. Grösse; 1 Behaarung, vergrössert; 2 Blüthe, etwas vergrössert; 3 dieselbe im Längsschnitt, stärker vergrössert; 4 aufgeschnittene Krone, desgl.; 5 Stempel, desgl.; 6 oberer Theil des Griffels mit Narbe, desgl.; 7 Staubgefässe, desgl.; 8 Pollen unter Wasser, desgl.; 9 abgeblühte Blüthe, desgl.; 10 Frucht, etwas vergrössert; 11 dieselbe im Querschnitt, stärker vergrössert; 12 Same, natürl. Grösse und vergrössert.  Latin: Nicotiana rustica.  Russian: Махорка. A — цветущее растение; 1 — волоски; 2 — цветок; 3 — то же в продольном разрезе; 4 — разрезанный венчик; 5 — пестик; 6 — верхняя часть столбика с рыльцем; 7 — тычинки; 8 — пыльца в воде; 9 — отцветший цветок; 10 — плод (коробочка); 11 — то же в поперечном разрезе; 12 — семя, в нат. величину и увелич.

ixodida-general;thumbnail2.creator: James Gathany
ixodida-general;thumbnail2.comments:
This photograph depicts a dorsal view of a female lone star tick, Amblyomma americanum. An ixodid or hard tick, A. americanum is found through the eastern and south-central states and can transmit disease agents that affect humans, dogs, goats, and white-tailed deer. Representatives from all three of its life stages aggressively bite people in the southern U.S. Lone star ticks transmit Ehrlichia chaffeensis and Ehrlichia ewingii, both of which cause disease. Borrelia lonestari, a pathogen associated with Southern tick-associated associated rash illness (STARI), also infects lone star ticks. Research suggests that up to 10% of the lone star ticks in an endemic area can be infected with any one of these pathogens. These ticks also are infected with a spotted-fever group Rickettsia, Rickettsia amblyommii but it is unknown at this time if this bacterium causes disease.
Created: 2006

ixodida-general;thumbnail3.creator: James Gathany
ixodida-general;thumbnail3.comments:
This photograph depicted ventral view of an engorged female "lone star tick" Amblyomma americanum. An Ixodes or "hard" tick, A. americanum is found through the southeast and south-central states, and has been shown to transmit the spirochete, Borrelia lonestari, the pathogen responsible for causing a Lyme disease-like rash known as "Southern tick-associated rash illness" (STARI). Representatives from all three of its life stages aggressively bite people in the southern U.S.
Created: 2006

tarentolaannularis-head;thumbnail3.creator: Matt Reinbold
tarentolaannularis-head;thumbnail3.comments: Lybbiya, or just Lybbi, is one of my oldest current pets, and one of only two that were here both before and after my time in the Air Force. She is a ringed wall gecko, Tarentola annularis. They're also known as white-spotted geckos, or white-spotted wall geckos. I've had her for at least seven years. She is relentlessly shy, skittish, and quick to bolt, but she's an amazingly voracious feeder.  This photo is also featured in the Encyclopedia of Life: www.eol.org/pages/790476

taeniasolium-general;thumbnail1.creator: Public Health Image Library
taeniasolium-general;thumbnail1.comments:
This 1973 image depicts two Taenia solium cysticerci, which represent the larval, or intermediate, immature developmental stages of this pork tapeworm.

Life cycle of Taenia saginata and T. solium (See PHIL 3420 for a illustrative diagram depicting the following life cycle):

Taeniasis is the infection of humans with the adult tapeworm of T. saginata or T. solium. Humans are the only definitive hosts for T. saginata and T. solium. Eggs or gravid proglottids are passed with feces; the eggs can survive for days to months in the environment. Cattle (T. saginata) and pigs (T. solium) become infected by ingesting vegetation contaminated with eggs or gravid proglottids. In the animal's intestine, the oncospheres hatch, invade the intestinal wall, and migrate to the striated muscles, where they develop into cysticerci. A cysticercus can survive for several years in the animal.
Created: 1973

perdicinae-general;thumbnail3.creator: Tatiana Bulyonkova
perdicinae-general;thumbnail3.comments: Perdix perdix - Grey Partridge - серая куропатка  I was walking past a field of peas and this large bird sprang from under my feet. I don't know who was scared the most! She started running around me, very fast, with one of her wings hanging like broken, and shouting loudly. Her chicks were chirping nearby. I hurried to leave, but took a few pictures of the bird circling like mad around me.

sesamumindicum-drawing;thumbnail3.creator: Franz Eugen Köhler, Köhler's Medizinal-Pflanzen
sesamumindicum-drawing;thumbnail3.comments: German: Sesam. A Wurzel. B Blühende und fruchttragende Pflanze. 1 Blüte, von der Seite gesehen; 2 Blüte im Längsschnitt; 3 Stempel; 3a Querschnitt des Stempels; 4 Reife Frucht im Aufspringen; 5, 6 Kapselhälften voneinander getrennt und geöffnet; 7 Samen der schwarzen Varietät; 8 Samen der weissen Varietät; 9 Samen im Längsschnitt; 10 Samen im Querschnitt; 11 Diagramm.  Latin: Sesamum indicum.  Russian: Кунжут. A — корень; B — растение с цветками и плодами; 1 — цветок, вид сбоку; 2 — цветок в продольном разрезе; 3 — пестик; 3a — пестик в поперечном разрезе; 4 — раскрывшийся плод (коробочка); 5, 6 — отделенные друг от друга и открытые половинки коробочки; 7 — семя черной разновидности; 8 — семя белой разновидности; 9 — семя в продольном разрезе; 10 — семя в поперечном разрезе; 11 — диаграмма цветка.
